snippet.textDisplay: More than anything, I think RuPaul needed AJ and the Queen to hit the reset button and give her image a much-needed boost from the damage of her controversial opinions and how cold she's (allegedly) become, particularly from Drag Race contestants.  If you need further convincing of this, take a look at any of Ru's clips from the 1990's.  She's a vastly different person now and in the game for an entirely different reason.  She's even mentioned how AJ and the Queen proved she still had a heart.  Ru has more than proven she's an unprecedented pop culture icon, but she's also proven how even the most beloved of them can too easily have the tide turn against them if they're not careful with their words or their actions.  Does she care?  Maybe.  Should she care?  Yes.

snippet.textDisplay: Love what she said about RuPaul. A lot of the newer generation of the LGBT community (particularly since Season 6 of Drag Race) have taken the community in a different direction than RuPaul and the originators of drag culture ever knew or learned how to operate amongst. I don’t think Ru comes from a place of hate with any of her disagreements or misunderstandings of these new ideologies and levels of social correctness... she’s just old school. And it sucks that so many of these kids try to demonize her when without her, drag would literally not even have a tenth of the exposure it has gained today and none of these girls would have had the ability to gain their followings and support system.

snippet.textDisplay: Drag race queens are put in a awkward situation when being on the show in that they don’t know or have any say in what footage is used, what storylines will play out.. Think of all the hours of unaired footage. Be aware that things get taken out of context or they can be fed drinks and so on... asked specific question... of course the queens can and do play their parts also and give the show makers what they want sometimes but at the end of it all it’s just a tv show for entertainment. There should never really be a reason to HATE any queen and just know like Valentina has shown here that most of the time they will be friends anyway regardless of what happened on camera. She is very classy and respectful in this video.. Some drag race fans should take notes.
